# Bypassing ASLR in Modern Kernels

## Introduction
Address Space Layout Randomization (ASLR) is a security technique used to prevent exploitation of memory corruption vulnerabilities...

### The Technique
By leveraging heap spraying and partial overwrites, we can reliably predict memory addresses even with randomization active.

```c
// Potential leak primitive
void leak_address() {
    // ...
}
```

### Conclusion
While ASLR remains a strong defense, it is not invincible when combined with other primitives.
